<subSubSection id="AE94119A86ED41FA35A3CBD9A992A1C6" pageId="null" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="DD07BE2B8FF0018ACFFBEC5DD4E4CFFF" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">
1 
<normalizedToken id="923D77F8E63A90618D25E7793ED3CF4F" originalValue="jährige" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">jaehrige</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="7A093E9DD3D913CFA0484CE14162C60F" originalValue="Kräuter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Kraeuter</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="F01BCDB5E270DD03994A2600DE256277" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
2-3fach fiederteilig; Zipfel schmal (0,5-2 mm breit); 
<normalizedToken id="90C1EECE9D11E5D7B9ABB3C9EF2E3225" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Blueten</normalizedToken>
aktinomorph, zwitterig, einzeln, 
<normalizedToken id="F8CA975B22B4B698330814922E713C5B" originalValue="endständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">endstaendig</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="25792246FD50B234A4ED39AC8D39017A" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
meist 5 (bei 
<taxonomicName id="58B586F476C14295969C0AC72E8B0286" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Nigella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="damascena">
<emphasis id="00DD09F3D20A2301B8F2935A1889BBDA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">N. damascena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bis 20), 
<normalizedToken id="E6E485A3649812C4739D9C9B5A368E49" originalValue="kronblattähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">kronblattaehnlich</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="D0A91389888A8E95A04024C2F4396A44" originalValue="spatelförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">spatelfoermig</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="D8B39120C643CB585D3DBA934C6E30E4" originalValue="Honigblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Honigblaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="F7B5355760A01143913EE2865561A6CF" originalValue="¼-½" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">1/4-1/2</normalizedToken>
so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="9F892E16A4B3C28E0FBE50F5DC18856A" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
, vor den 
<normalizedToken id="D28A0771FAE3CD194E20F3289FBBAED0" originalValue="Perigonblättern" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Perigonblaettern</normalizedToken>
stehend, 
<normalizedToken id="D57B7065BCAE02CF401E7732EFF6C96D" originalValue="becherförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">becherfoermig</normalizedToken>
, 21ippig (Ober- und Unterlippe). 
<normalizedToken id="755CCB493F90D89F419340E59032904B" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
zahlreich. 
<emphasis id="DDE4DA4C5ACA5853EAF6806B86FBF56A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">
<normalizedToken id="287DC2A9EAEFA5A54D0B6D2A5234CBA2" originalValue="Fruchtblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Fruchtblaetter</normalizedToken>
2-10, zur 
<normalizedToken id="1EF593727B8D534E578A7E1DB1E90DFE" originalValue="Hälfte" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Haelfte</normalizedToken>
bis 
<normalizedToken id="2848770E4C55E9081DD8D6B5DCE20286" originalValue="vollständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">vollstaendig</normalizedToken>
miteinander verwachsen
</emphasis>
(bei den 
<taxonomicName id="F934B8D55C8E679A441005F37B4B66DB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
<emphasis id="6D79D26804B94C871DE4A35635108D34" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Ranunculaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sonst nur noch bei 
<taxonomicName id="E1F3C69FEBB892EBF02C4BB9FAC0D085" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Helleborus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="82FD2A41D1D973965523FE56711A0EF1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Helleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
am Grunde verwachsen), aufgeblasen, mehrsamig; Narben lang 
<normalizedToken id="45B95CD8C1993284FA9CE0731097E9CC" originalValue="geschnäbelt" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">geschnaebelt</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE379E47B2FA1C30D0C1FC809B8C62C7" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="179DE00A93CAF16F471CA79B86C40E13" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="EEB66B38F43464BB64FCD6D0D1A07990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Nigella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="null" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Nigella</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="329BB6B64C69F83C617CD38094279956" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 25 Arten, die in 
<normalizedToken id="9A5E132FED577FDFDEB56CC53A8F0236" originalValue="Südeuropa" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Suedeuropa</normalizedToken>
, Nordafrika und Westasien verbreitet sind.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1D824BE33A2C74512E9F9C9FF267AF0" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">
Polyploidie ist in der Gattung unbekannt. Von 10 Arten haben 9 Arten 2n = 12, 1 Art 2n = 14. 
<normalizedToken id="9B0E7C6181635F71F9B03F56B4B3F548" originalValue="Sterilität" pageId="null" pageNumber="34">Sterilitaet</normalizedToken>
zwischen den Arten ist die Regel (Gregory 1941).
</paragraph>
